description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF supported the development of an advocacy and communication plan to increase enrollment of Roma children in preschool education building on the assessment results conducted in nine local communities. This plan will be used by UNICEF and other members of the REYN network for advocacy purposes and planning targeted interventions. TV content as alternative delivery of preschool curricula was produced and broadcasted on state television reaching 30,000 children. The investment case for children - feasibility study on financing options for full preschool education coverage started its inception phase. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
